{
  "stem": "18102.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And Bobble and I would go for very long walks in the-- in the forest.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "These were very, very tall oak trees and pine trees.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was a real comfortable feeling of having her hold my hand as we walked and talked.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Children talk, I'm sure, because she was probably accommodating me during this-- these kinds of interludes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I remember them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They stand out in my mind.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so I really loved her and my grandmother, who was my safety valve, my grandmother would give me breakfast and lunch and later on, of course, dinner when my parents would come back to the house.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we would have dinner in the evening.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Bubbe.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I recall, of course, the cholent, which was a favorite of mine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that would be a stew that would have to sit in the oven for 24 hours without stirring.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it had all kinds of ingredients in it that was very good to my taste anyway.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the thing that I loved the most was even more than the cholent, which would be a daily food herring.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I-- I enjoyed herring with the Bialystok kuchen as I mentioned.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my grandmother knew that for me the tail of the herring was the most important part.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she would give me that, because I wouldn't have to hold a fork.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You could hold the tail and eat it by holding the tail, rather than a piece in the middle which you needed a fork to eat the herring with.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that's how she'd give it to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, of course, the Bialystok kuchen, which became world famous-- you know, that's where the word bialy comes from-- would be my favorite meal with the herring.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's what my grandmother gave me.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
